synthesis_method: The electrolyte synthesis process involved preparing a positive electrode mixture by mixing elemental sulfur, GeS2, and VGCF in specified weight ratios, ball milling the mixture for 48 hours, followed by assembling an all-solid-state battery by pressing a solid electrolyte layer, a positive electrode layer with the mixture, and a negative electrode layer with lithium metal foil, resulting in the final all-solid battery with Al foil on the positive electrode side and Cu foil on the negative electrode side.
